-- Wal-Mart Won't Raise Massmart Price for Minorties, Business Day Reports
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-11-04T12:03:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/wal-mart-won-t-raise-massmart-price-for-minorties-bus-day-says.html
Wal-Mart Stores Inc. won’t raise its
offer price for Massmart Holdings Ltd. to buyout minority
shareholders and will not accept less than 50 percent of the
South African retailer, Business Day said, citing Wal-Mart
International Chief Executive Officer Doug McMillon.  Wal-Mart was willing to work with large Massmart
shareholders who want to remain invested in the company, the
Johannesburg-based said on its website, cited comments from
McMillon at a briefing in the city today.   Wal-Mart aims to complete the transaction early next year,
Business Day said, citing Andy Bond, Wal-Mart’s executive vice-
president responsible for the U.K. and Africa.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  